node.text: #FireEcology (WILDFIRES) with US Forest Service scientist Dr. Gavin Jones is up! Megafires, how plants have adapted, hospitable wombats, how fire has changed in the last century, mosaic ecosystems, prescribed burns, and hooting at owls for science. Also: tales of burning romance & arson. Have you ever had to evacuate for a fire? Make sure to read the motel reviews first.

node.text: Ooooh #SystemsBiology (MEDICAL MATHEMATICS) with Dr. Emily Ackerman is up! How do our bodies make math? How do graphs and data help us understand everything from inflammation to influenza to COVID-19. Graphs, code, triplicate experiments, animal models vs. future computing, disability and accessibility in STEM. Dr. Ackerman is brilliant, hilarious and warm and you’ll dig her. Link in bio!

There’s tremendous diversity amongst fireflies. Not all fireflies fly.  Not all sparklebutts sparkle. Some eat snails, others throw down nectar. Some are tiny. Some don’t have mouths. Some are critically endangered.

Scroll through to see a small sampling of the 2,000+ firefly species, including the critically endangered Bethany Beach firefly (7) and the firefly larva preying on a snail (10).

Lampyridology aka Sparklebuttology (FIREFLIES) with @silentsparks is up now! Link in bio.

node.text:
Thoughts on catching and releasing fireflies?

"I love that people catch fireflies and then release them. It's a beautiful thing. I think the more people that can appreciate these miraculous luminous beings, the better. What better way to do it than to get up close and personal with them? As long as people realize that if you catch a firefly, catch it with a net, handle it really gently, coax it into a jar with some grass, maybe a little bit of damp (not sopping wet) paper towel, even a little tiny piece of apple -- they'll really, really like the moisture from the apple and the sugars that are in the apple. Watch them overnight, make sure they have a lot of moisture in the jar, then let them go into the same habitat where you collected them the next day." -Dr. Sara Lewis @silentsparks, Lampyridology (FIREFLIES)

An illuminating episode on ✨FIREFLIES✨ is up now! Link in bio. Photo by @stevendavidjohnsonphoto
